We recommended that the following measures shall be effected to ensure effective internal control over cash advances for SEF:

The Accountant should not grant additional cash advances to any official or employee unless the previous cash advance is first settled or a proper accounting thereof is made;
He/she shall not grant cash advances when found to have incomplete supporting documents particularly pertaining to authority to draw a cash advance outside the personnel’s area of jurisdiction;
The Head of the Agency shall ensure that the personnel, to which the cash advance is granted, does not exceed the maximum amount of his/her accountability.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive through the members of the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board (MSWMB) adopt the following courses of action:

Stop the operation of open dumpsite;
Procure additional recycling equipment not limited to non-biodegradable only and cost efficient;
Fully equip the MRF; 
Strictly enforce the waste segregation policy; and
Find a Sanitary Landfill or long-term storage facility.

